    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense, but some of these drops are so sudden though. like, in some of these more remote areas, the records just seem to go totally dark or the numbers just vanish without even a mention of a war or a fever. it feels like there's a huge gap in the data where people just... disappeared. do historians usually just attribute that to bad record keeping or is there something else that could cause such a massive, unexplained loss of people in a short time?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
